<div>
    <h1 class="bux-h1 bux-mar-top-sp-16">My Labs</h1>

    <p>
        Welcome to the lab page. We do research at the intersection of natural language
        processing, machine learning, and responsible AI. Below you will find our research
        areas, people, lab expectations, and how to join my lab.
    </p>

    <h2>Research Areas</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Natural Language Processing</li>
        <li>Language Model Evaluation & Alignment</li>
        <li>Multilingual & Tokenization Methods</li>
        <li>Robustness and Safety of AI systems</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Prospective Students</h2>
    <div class="prospective">
        <p>
            This section provides context for potential PhD students on what I am interested in. If you believe we may be a good fit, I encourage you to apply to OSU (and include my name as a potential advisor in the application).
        </p>

        <p>
            My primary field of research lies broadly in the intersection of natural language + AI. Within this space, I am primarily interested in developing and studying human-centered language technologies — NLP models, language models, and systems centered around human needs and preferences rather than solely focused on capabilities. Please check out my recent publications to learn more.
        </p>

        <h3>If you are interested in joining my lab</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Already at / accepted to OSU CSE Ph.D. program:</strong> Please feel free to reach out via email.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Applying to the Ph.D. program:</strong> I hire Ph.D. students through the OSE CSE PhD program — see the department's admission page for details. Select me as a potential advisor on your application form and mention my name in the final paragraph of your Statement of Purpose. I will read all applications that mention my name.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Already an accepted MS or undergraduate student at OSU:</strong> Please feel free to reach out via email. I expect you to have completed courses like linear algebra (Math 2568), AI (CSE 3521), and/or some more advanced courses (CSE 5523/5524/5525/5526) or be familiar with the concepts from these courses.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Culture, values, and expectations</h3>
        <p>
            I do not expect incoming students to have extensive experience in ML/NLP, but students should be comfortable writing Python and familiar with libraries such as PyTorch and Huggingface Transformers. I strive to maintain a lab that values inclusiveness and is a safe environment for all members. I expect to work closely with students (regular meetings, active involvement in projects, help with paper writing). While I expect frequent communication, I do not track work hours or vacation time — students set schedules that best support their mental health and productivity.
        </p>

        <p>
            If you'd like to reach out, email: <a href="kumar.1145@osu.edu">kumar.1145@osu.edu</a>
        </p>

    </div>

    <h2>People</h2>
    <div class="people-grid">
        <% (data.prof_group.group || []).each do |p| %>
            <div class="person"> 
                <%# prefer local image files named FirstNameLastName.(png|jpg|jpeg) in source/images, else fall back to p.image %>
                <% local_basename = "#{p.first_name}#{p.last_name}".gsub(/\s+/, '') %>
                <% local_src = nil %>
                <% ['.png', '.jpg', '.jpeg'].each do |ext| %>
                  <% candidate = File.join(Dir.pwd, 'source', 'images', "#{local_basename}#{ext}") %>
                  <% if File.exist?(candidate) %>
                    <% local_src = "/images/#{local_basename}#{ext}" %>
                    <% break %>
                  <% end %>
                <% end %>
                <% img_src = local_src || (p.image && p.image != '' ? p.image : nil) %>
                <% if img_src %>
                    <img src="<%= img_src %>" alt="<%= "#{p.first_name} #{p.last_name}" %>" style="max-width:140px; display:block; margin-bottom:6px;">
                <% end %>
                <h3>
                    <% if p.webpage && p.webpage != "" %>
                        <a href="<%= p.webpage %>"><%= "#{p.first_name} #{p.last_name}" %></a>
                    <% else %>
                        <%= "#{p.first_name} #{p.last_name}" %>
                    <% end %>
                </h3>
                <p><%= p.role %> <%= "(#{p.start_year})" if p.start_year %></p>
                <% if p.notes && p.notes != "" %>
                    <p class="muted"><%= p.notes %></p>
                <% end %>
            </div>
        <% end %>
    </div>

    <% if data.prof_group.alumni && data.prof_group.alumni.any? %>
        <h3>Alumni</h3>
        <div class="alumni-grid">
            <% data.prof_group.alumni.each do |a| %>
                <div class="alumni-person" style="display:inline-block; margin:8px; text-align:center;">
                    <%# prefer local image files named FirstNameLastName.(png|jpg|jpeg) in source/images, else fall back to a.image %>
                    <% local_basename = "#{a.first_name}#{a.last_name}".gsub(/\s+/, '') %>
                    <% local_src = nil %>
                    <% ['.png', '.jpg', '.jpeg'].each do |ext| %>
                      <% candidate = File.join(Dir.pwd, 'source', 'images', "#{local_basename}#{ext}") %>
                      <% if File.exist?(candidate) %>
                        <% local_src = "/images/#{local_basename}#{ext}" %>
                        <% break %>
                      <% end %>
                    <% end %>
                    <% img_src = local_src || (a.image && a.image != '' ? a.image : nil) %>
                    <% if img_src %>
                      <img src="<%= img_src %>" alt="<%= "#{a.first_name} #{a.last_name}" %>" style="max-width:100px; display:block; margin:0 auto 6px;">
                    <% end %>
                    <div style="font-weight:600;"><%= "#{a.first_name} #{a.last_name}" %></div>
                    <% if a.role %><div style="font-size:0.9rem; color:#666;"><em><%= a.role %></em></div><% end %>
                    <% if a.notes && a.notes != "" %><div style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#666;">(<%= a.notes %>)</div><% end %>
                </div>
            <% end %>
        </div>
    <% end %>

</div>
